race.comment: DAUFUSKIE ISLAND (3) was safely held when fourth last time out over 1308m at Timonium, beaten 4.5 lengths. That followed a win at Colonial Downs at the previous outing. Will enjoy a drop in class so he is a leading player. SLIPPIN JIMMY (2) made progress last time out, finishing 2.25 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1106m at Colonial Downs after being in contention on the bend. Jevian Toledo gets the best out of this nine-year-old gelding. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. NOBLE JON (5) is a 13-time winner who has been performing well, beaten 2.75 lengths into third last time out over 1106m at this track. Well placed and is a solid top-three chance. FREESTANDING (15) did a great job to score by 0.8 lengths over this course and distance last start in a nice progression on the first-up run. Looks well placed so expect another big run. Something for the Multiples: PIT STOP MAN (7) ISLAND D'LITE (11)
